description.narrative:
The overall objective of project is to generate consensus among regional stakeholders on how Afghanistan’s Central Asian neighbors may use their influence in support of the Afghan peace negotiations to achieve a just and enduring end to the 40-year-old Afghan conflict.
The two specific objectives are:
1) To discuss the security concerns of Kazakhstan, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan, Tajikistan, and Kyrgyzstan during the ongoing Afghan peace process and following the conclusion of infra-Afghan negotiations and to clarify the security guarantees and mechanisms of cooperation the countries see as necessary under both scenarios in the areas of counter-terrorism, fight against organized crime, and countering violent extremism (CVE); and
2) To exchange insights and ideas on issues and questions of longer-term significance with a focus on how Afghanistan and Kazakhstan, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan, Tajikistan, and Kyrgyzstan can work together to realize closer economic cooperation at the bilateral and regional levels, including the vision of regional economic integration between Central Asia and South Asia via Afghanistan.
The expected outcomes are:
Established Track 2 and 1.5 platform for dialogue between Afghanistan and Central Asian countries;
Improved Central Asian countries’ engagement in the Afghan peace process;
Increased policy and public awareness about the peace process and broader regional challenges and opportunities;
Increased regional cooperation and common efforts for regional consensus on peace and stability in Afghanistan.
